lobbying_activities: [{'general_issue_code': 'AGR', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Agriculture', 'description': 'Promote plant based and bio-based policies for the farm bill, re-authorization of the Agriculture Improvement Act of 2018, as well as other areas such as the National Defense Authorization Act re-authorization and appropriations. Support CRA\'s Plant Based Products Council and Ag Bioeconomy Coalition broad agendas. Specific focus on the USDA "biopreferred" program (sec. 9002), the "biorefinery, renewable chemical and biobased products" program including adding biobased terminology, (sec. 9003) of the farm bill, including adding back in a competitive grants sub-program (that was removed in a prior farm bill) to the latter program for pilot and demonstration scale biobased facilities. Support bioeconomy research generally. In the NDAA consider a biobased products acceleration effort that supports and enhances the 9002 biopreferred program, a biobased procurement law for the entire Federal government.
